My oldest son (senior, ASU, aero-engineering) just texted me. He's pretty far right, but not a big Charlie fan (nothing negative, just not particularly a fan). Anyway:

"It took a couple weeks, but I'm finally feeling Charlie's passing. I guess I finally saw enough compilations of lefty celebrations.

I think the one that finally got me is one where this chick says, "the best part is that he wasn't martyr material." She doesn't have the usual signs of mental illness. No dyed hair, no visible dumb tattoo, no nose ring, not dressed like a whore. She looks like she even has a wedding/engagement ring.

I think what gets me is that she's right. He isn't martyr material. Him getting shot isn't what really distresses me. It's the death celebration that turned him into a martyr. If she and every homicidal lefty like her had the decency to mourn the loss of a regular guy, he might have just been a blip in a wikipedia page about 2020s conservative media personalities. But she didn't, and now we're all Charlie Kirk."
